Constructor Detail

Album.AclEntry

public Album.AclEntry(java.lang.String accessorType,
                      java.lang.String accessorInfo,
                      java.lang.String accessType,
                      java.lang.String accessorId)
Create a new Album.AclEntry. To share an album, create a new Album.AclEntry and add it to a Album.AccessControlList. Set the Album.AccessControlList in Album using Album.setAccessControlList(AccessControlList). Finally call AlbumsTxFactory.updateAlbum(Album). 
   acl = album.getAccessControlList();
   // ..
   // ..
   AclEntry newAcl = new AclEntry(Constants.AlbumAccessorType.EXTERNAL,
       "blah@bleh.bloh",
       Constants.AlbumAccessType.READ,
       "");
   acl.addAclEntry(newAcl);
   album.setAccessControlList(acl);
   // ..
   updateTx = albumsTxFatory.update(album);
   // .. add to batch and send to server

Parameters:
accessorType - see Constants.AlbumAccessorType for valid values
accessorInfo - phone number or email address (if applicable)
accessType - see Constants.AlbumAccessType for valid values
accessorId - the id of the accessor; used when the accessor type is user
Method Detail

getAccessType

public java.lang.String getAccessType()
The type of access granted by this Album.AclEntry. Valid values are in Constants.AlbumAccessType.

getAccessorInfo

public java.lang.String getAccessorInfo()
The email address or phone number of the accessor. This is only applicable if accessor type is email or phone number.

See Also:
getAccessorType()

getAccessorType

public java.lang.String getAccessorType()
Returns the type of accessor defined by this Album.AclEntry. Valid values are in Constants.AlbumAccessorType. Depending on accessor type, related values are had through getAccessorInfo() or getAccessorId().

getAccessorId

public java.lang.String getAccessorId()
The userid of the user with access. This is present if accessor type is Constants.AlbumAccessorType.USER.
